richtungen und ihre jeweils spezifischen Herausforderungen zeigen sich nicht nur Differenzen, sondern auch Parallelen und Schnittstellen einer heterogenen Archivlandschaft.  aThe book discusses various forms of archives. What does it mean when there is only a single archive holder? What about literary estates held in libraries and storage facilities of museum institutions or in administrative archives? The various types of archival institutions differ from one another yet also share parallels and intersections.  afunded by Adalbert-Stifter-Institut  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aBibliography. Library science. Information resources. 0aDiplomatics. Archives. Seals. 0aLiterature (General). 4aArchiv. 4aNachlassinventar. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / General.2bisacsh  aArchives.  aliterary estate inventories.1 aBaßler, Moritz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBenne, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuchmayr, Friedrich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDallinger, Petra-Maria, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFolie, Sabine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFörster, Joachim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGaisbauer, Stephan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGerhalter, Li, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHofer, Georg, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHuber, Mario, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabula